<HEADLINE>
<P>
KING JURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rodney King jury correctly applied the laws on punitive damages (June 2). 
The objective is to punish the defendants and deter them.The poorer the 
wrongdoer, the smaller the award need be. Valid punitive damage awards are no 
more than a fraction of the defendants' net worth. Laurence Powell and Stacey 
Koon are destitute. An award of zero shows more common sense and legal 
correctness than millions (legally invalid) or $5, a fraction of their net 
worth. The jurors deserve our thanks for the right stuff. 
</P>
<P>
 D. EARL ELLIS 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Palisades 
</P>
<P>
 * Based on what I read in "King Jury's Voice of Reason Carried a Private 
Burden" (June 3), I think the forewoman, Ester Soriano-Hewitt, not only did a 
very difficult and professional job in working with the jurors in this case, 
but she did something far more important. 
</P>
<P>
 She was able to put her own personal feelings secondary to resolving the case 
for the good of the whole. She considered that there was more than one point of 
view. 
</P>
<P>
 This is a major problem throughout the world today. Factions are trying to 
"get even." If they would get the chip off their shoulder and truly negotiate, 
the world would calm down significantly. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM CHANTLAND 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
