<P>
GERMAN SENTENCED FOR DESECRATING CEMETERIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A court Thursday sentenced a man to 2 years and 3 months in prison for 
desecrating a Jewish cemetery, a Nazi concentration camp cemetery and a 
Holocaust memorial. 
</P>
<P>
 The defendant, a 24-year-old baker, was the fourth to be jailed in the 
anti-Semitic incidents near Constance on the Swiss border in October, 1992. 
</P>
