<HEADLINE>
<P>
EX-PREMIER OF GREECE FACES WIRETAP TRIAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Greek Parliament voted Thursday to place former conservative prime 
minister Constantine Mitsotakis on trial for his alleged role in a major 
phone-tapping scandal. 
</P>
<P>
 The 300-seat body voted 163-6 to lift Mitsotakis' parliamentary immunity and 
ordered him to be tried on charges in connection with a scheme to wiretap 
dozens of political opponents and journalists from 1988 to 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 A 13-member special court, made up of Supreme Court judges, will be formed to 
try him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
