<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CONFESS TO KILLING ANTI-MOB LAWMAKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two small-time drug dealers confessed Thursday to killing a French lawmaker 
who crusaded against organized crime and its ties to local politics on the 
Riviera. 
</P>
<P>
 The pair were among about 30 people rounded up Wednesday in the latest sweep 
by police in Toulon, near Marseilles, since Yann Piat was killed Feb. 25. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman's slaying threw a spotlight on links between the mob, politics and 
business on the Riviera, raising the specter of the sort of corruption that has 
long plagued Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
