<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: FILLMORE; INSURER HONORS BUS FIRM'S SAFETY RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Nearly 1 million accident-free miles logged by drivers for Fillmore Area 
Transit have been rewarded by the company's insurance carrier at a small 
ceremony.  
</P>
<P>
 The private bus company received a Gold Safety award from the New York-based 
Lancer Insurance Co. for avoiding fender-benders and more serious accidents for 
the past five years. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're very proud of the fact that we have a good safety record," said Jeri 
Morris, president of the eight-bus transit company. "It takes a lot of time and 
effort to keep our employees up to date on regulations." 
</P>
<P>
 Driver Phil White said his key to safe driving is to always pay attention. 
</P>
<P>
 "You have to be aware of what's around you and always be aware of what's ahead 
of you," said White, a retired driver for a parcel delivery company who has 
worked part time for Fillmore Area Transit for 10 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Tex Jennings, a FAT driver since 1987, said he has avoided accidents for 
almost 20 years. 
</P>
<P>
 "When I came to work here seven years ago, my DMV rap sheet had nothing to 
report," said Jennings, who logged hundreds of miles a week when he worked as a 
traveling salesman in his younger days. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've had a lot of near-misses, so I consider myself lucky," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fillmore Area Transit operates eight buses five days a week along three 
different routes. More than 50,000 riders a year board the buses, Morris said. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents can take the central city commuter, which travels throughout 
Fillmore several times each day. Another bus shuttles people to Piru and back, 
and a third route travels to Santa Paula and Ventura. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
