 Firefighters put out the blaze at 64 James Drive, saving the structure. 
</P>
<P>
 The home at 60 James had about $150,000 in property loss and $75,000 in damage 
to contents, including the motor home, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The only injury was to a man who jumped in to help put out the blaze. Derick 
Henderson received slight flash burns on his shoulder, but was treated at the 
scene by firefighters, authorities said. KAY SAILLANT 
