<HEADLINE>
<P>
TIME FOR SOCIETY TO MOTHER MOMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thank you for Shari Roan's "The Fourth Trimester" (May 24). Roan clarifies the 
distorted assumption that women recover from childbirth in four to six weeks. 
</P>
<P>
 Our culture has lost the time-honored traditions of "mothering the mother." 
Consequently, we have seen a rise in postpartum mood disorders and family 
crises due to childbirth. 
</P>
<P>
 As a response to this, Jewish Family Services has a support group, "New Moms," 
which brings mothers together to nurture each other and provides information 
and referrals to address symptoms of postpartum depression and anxiety. 
</P>
<P>
 DVORA KRAVITZ 
</P>
<P>
 Staff Therapist 
</P>
<P>
 Jewish Family Service 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
