<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; MAN WHO 
SET MOTHER OF HIS CHILDREN AFIRE GETS LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A cocaine addict who set the mother of his two young children on fire has been 
sentenced to life in prison. 
</P>
<P>
 Superior Court Judge Candace Beason imposed the sentence Wednesday on Johnny 
Mack Finney, 38.He was on probation for attacking his ex-wife when he set fire 
to Janice Johnson, his live-in companion and mother of his two children. 
</P>
<P>
 Finney poured a soda bottle filled with gasoline on the woman, then flicked a 
cigarette lighter while her 15-year-old son looked on in horror. Johnson 
suffered third-degree burns from her chest to her head. One ear was burned off 
in the Aug. 1, 1993, attack at their suburban Val Verde home. 
</P>
<P>
 Finney held the victim down by sitting on her legs while her body was afire, 
Deputy Dist. Atty. Jon Jonas said. 
</P>
<P>
 A friend who heard her screams smothered the flames by wrapping himself around 
Johnson. Finney, an admitted cocaine addict, apologized when he was convicted 
June 1 of attempted murder, assault with a deadly weapon causing great bodily 
injury, and corporal battery on a spouse. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Public Defender Howard Waco argued that Finney was drunk and unable to 
think clearly. But the prosecutor said Finney had passed a fellow inmate a 
playing card with the note: "I set (her) on fire. She deserved it." 
</P>
</TEXT>
