</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two young men, described as being clean-cut and in their 20s, are suspected of 
being involved in a series of muggings in the last two weeks in the Tarzana 
area, Los Angeles police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses reported that the two men carried a .45-caliber handgun and drove a 
pale yellow Cadillac, said Senior Lead Officer Ken Knox. 
</P>
<P>
 The latest in the series of three muggings occurred Thursday morning in the 
4800 block of Brewster Avenue, where a female real estate agent was waiting for 
her clients outside a house. 
</P>
