-- which reported assets of $500 million in May -- leased the site for $7 
million over a 12-year period. 
</P>
<P>
 The firm decided to move to Glendale from its location at 300 E. Magnolia 
Blvd. because it plans to expand its operations by one-third, said Gary Brent, 
senior vice president of savings and administrative services. JENNIFER OLDHAM 
