of the Warner Bros. movies "Maverick" and "Wyatt Earp." 
</P>
<P>
 Employees are starting to move in and should be finished by July 1, said Dan 
Garcia, company vice president of real estate and public affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 "The thought was that our company was growing and absorbing a significant 
amount of leasehold space," Garcia said. "We owned the property (at Olive and 
Pass) and thought it was appropriate to develop this corner of our property." 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia declined to reveal how much the multimillion-dollar project cost. 
