<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD CUP USA '94 / THE FIRST ROUND; WORLD CUP AT A GLANCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * WHAT 
</P>
<P>
 The World Cup, the championship of soccer, is a monthlong tournament beginning 
today with two games and ending with the July 17 title game in the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 * WHO 
</P>
<P>
 Twenty-two nations qualified, joining the defending champion (Germany) and the 
host (United States).The 24 teams are divided into six groups. 
</P>
<P>
 * WHERE 
</P>
<P>
 Pasadena, Palo Alto, Dallas, Chicago, Washington, East Rutherford, N.J.; 
Foxboro, Mass.; Orlando, Fla; Pontiac, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
 * TODAY'S GAMES 
</P>
<P>
 Germany vs. Bolivia at Soldier Field in Chicago, 11:55 a.m. PDT, ESPN, 
Univision; Spain vs. South Korea at the Cotton Bowl in Dallas, 4:35 p.m., 
ESPN2, Univision. 
</P>
<P>
 * FIRST U.S. GAME 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. vs. Switzerland, Saturday at the Silverdome in Pontiac, Mich.; 8:30 a.m., 
Channel 7, Univision. 
</P>
<P>
 * FIRST ROSE BOWL GAME 
</P>
<P>
 Colombia vs. Romania, Saturday, 4:30 p.m., ESPN, Univision. 
</P>
