<HEADLINE>
<P>
INSIDE LINE: DINNER DATES; OC HIGH / STUDENT NEWS AND VIEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If you could invite three famous people, dead or alive, to dinner, who would 
they be and why? 
</P>
<P>
 Here are some of the responses to that question published by the Wildcat, the 
student newspaper at Brea Olinda High School: 
</P>
<P>
 * Jimi Hendrix, so he can teach me some licks.Albert Einstein, so he can teach 
me the theory of relativity, and Bill Clinton, so I can teach him how to run 
the country. 
</P>
<P>
 * Dan Quayle, so I can teach him how to spell potato; Hillary Clinton, because 
everybody says she's so smart, and Bill Clinton, so I can tell him how smart 
he's not. 
</P>
<P>
 * Leslie Nielsen because he can keep a straight face while saying something 
funny; Tom Jones, because he's just a happening guy, and Bruce Lee, because 
he's a martial arts stud. 
