made public this week. 
</P>
<P>
 In April, 1993, D'Amato told reporters Thursday, he took his entire retirement 
savings, worth $19,324, from an individual retirement account and gave it to 
David Beall, 20, the son-in-law of a friend, to invest as he wished. 
</P>
