<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; VIRGINIA; ABORTION CLINIC ACCESS LAW UPHELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A federal judge rejected an anti-abortion group's arguments and upheld a new 
law that bars protesters from blocking the entrances of abortion clinics. U.S. 
District Judge Leonie Brinkema of Alexandria rejected the claim of the American 
Life League Inc. that the law is too vague and violates the right of free 
speech. The ruling was the first to come out of several challenges that 
anti-abortion activists have filed against the law. 
</P>
