ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SEAL BEACH; COUNCIL TO VOTE ON PARK EQUIPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHELBY GRAD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council will vote June 27 on a plan to add a volleyball court and new 
playground equipment to Edison Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The plan has divided the College Park West neighborhood.Some residents argue 
that the 30-year-old park needs improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 But others, whose homes back up to the park, fear that the volleyball court 
will attract loud youths. 
</P>
<P>
 The Parks Commission voted last month to support the proposal, which was 
submitted by a group of residents who also are raising money to pay for the 
improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 The group said Edison Park could be more valuable to residents if a sand 
volleyball court is built and the aging metal jungle gym is replaced by a more 
modern playground. 
</P>
<P>
 More than $8,000 has been raised to pay for some of the improvements. 
</P>
<P>
 Project opponents complained that the park already generates too much noise. 
</P>
<P>
 They have asked the city to add lights to the park and increase security 
patrols.SHELBY GRAD 
