<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 68% AT SCHOOL PASS PHYSICAL FITNESS TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Heritage Oak Private Elementary School has announced that a record 68% of its 
kindergarten-through-sixth-grade students recently qualified for Presidential 
Physical Fitness Awards. 
</P>
<P>
 This could be the highest percentage in the state, according to curriculum 
director Elizabeth Holloman, who said Heritage Oak finished a close second to a 
Temecula school in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year, 64% of Heritage Oak students earned the award. Statewide results 
are expected in October. 
</P>
<P>
 "This year, I think we have it," said Holloman, who credited physical 
education instructor Leonard Johnson with dramatically increasing the fitness 
of students over the past five years. 
</P>
<P>
 Before Johnson began the training program, less than 20% of the students 
passed the nationally certified test, Holloman said. "It's amazing to see how 
much better they are physically," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 To get the students in shape, Johnson instituted a program of running, 
pushups, pullups, relays and other activities. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
