ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; KIDNAPING SUSPECT SOUGHT BY POLICE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police were searching for a 32-year-old man who allegedly kidnaped his son at 
gunpoint during a domestic dispute Thursday morning, then returned the boy 
unharmed three hours later, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 At 8:15 a.m., Elias Garcia Vidal forced his way into the apartment of 
37-year-old Maria Melendez in the 1000 block of West Highland Street, police 
said.Melendez, who had obtained a restraining order from a judge against Vidal, 
was in the apartment with their two children, Sgt. Dick Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 Vidal "brandished a handgun and Melendez and her daughter ran for safety," 
Faust said. "Vidal then took his 4-year-old son from the residence." 
</P>
<P>
 Fearing Vidal had fled to Mexico, police searched for him and the boy, who has 
the same name as his father. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe the father returned to the area about 11:15 a.m. in a different 
car than the white 1983 Buick he was originally seen driving. He managed to 
drop the child off near Melendez's apartment complex without being noticed, 
Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 The child was reunited with his mother, who declined to talk about the 
incident. 
</P>
<P>
 "At least there was a happy ending," Faust said.GREG HERNANDEZ 
</P>
