ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: IRVINE; TRAFFIC CRASH FATAL TO 2 UCI STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK PINSKY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two UC Irvine students were fatally hurt just after noon Thursday when their 
compact car crossed a double center line on Campus Drive and crashed head-on 
into a freight truck, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The students were identified as Abbette Rodriguez, 19, of Oceanside and Ritika 
Rajasanhsi, also 19, of Fremont, according to the county coroner's office. 
</P>
<P>
 Both women, who were suite mates on the UCI campus, had to be cut out of the 
car they were riding in, Lt. Sam Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 The car came to rest in the westbound lane of Campus Drive, in the marshy area 
between University Drive and Jamboree Road, not far from the campus. 
</P>
<P>
 Rajasanhsi, who was a passenger in the car, was pronounced dead at the scene. 
Rodriguez, the driver, died 1 1/2 hours later at Irvine Medical Center, 
Allevato said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rajasanhsi was studying social sciences, and Rodriguez was studying physical 
sciences. Both were freshmen. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the truck, which came to rest in the eastbound bicycle lane, was 
not injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said that the cause of the accident was under investigation but that it 
did not appear that drugs or alcohol were a factor. MARK PINSKY 
</P>
</TEXT>
