MAN HELD IN BANK ROBBERY, CARJACKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man suspected of robbing a bank Thursday was also was booked on suspicion of 
a carjacking in Huntington Beach last week. 
</P>
<P>
 The bank robbery occurred at 1:30 p.m. at the Bank of America branch in the 
2600 block of North Tustin Avenue, Lt. Timm Browne said.The robber handed a 
teller a note demanding money, and escaped with an undetermined amount. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers looking for the robber found the suspect nearby in a car that had 
been reported stolen in a carjacking in Huntington Beach, Browne said. They 
also found a large amount of cash in the car. 
</P>
<P>
 Dennis Fitzgerald Dearmore, 25, of Long Beach was arrested on suspicion of 
robbery and carjacking and taken to Orange County Jail, Browne said. 
