BRIEFLY: LABOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Caterpillar Strike Threatened: The United Auto Workers union said it will 
strike plants nationwide if a labor dispute is not resolved by Tuesday.The 
union also asked federal mediators to schedule immediate meetings to address 
what it called unfair labor practices by the Peoria, Ill.-based company. The 
UAW said its 14,500 Caterpillar workers will strike if the meetings fail to 
resolve the conflict that has led to nine walkouts since September. "Our 
members are being illegally disciplined, suspended, fired and locked out," said 
Jerry Baker, chairman of the UAW central bargaining committee. UAW members have 
been working without a contract under terms of Caterpillar's final offer, 
imposed in April, 1992. 
