</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CYP International, an architectural and planning firm, said Thursday it has 
won a contract to design a $100-million hotel and apartment complex in downtown 
St. Petersburg, Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 The eight-story Hotel Rafael will blend with the "unique historic 
architecture" in St. Petersburg's city center, said Donald R. Corbin, CYP's 
chairman.The 350,000-square-foot structure will consist of 150 guest rooms on 
the first four floors and one- to three-bedroom apartments on the top four 
floors, he said. 
</P>
<P>
 The hotel, a joint venture by two British companies, will be near the famous 
Maryinsky Theatre, which is home to the Kirov Ballet. 
</P>
<P>
 CYP must move quickly to draw the plans because construction is scheduled to 
begin late this year. IHS Hawaii Inc. will provide materials and supplies for 
the hotel, and a Finnish company will build it. 
</P>
<P>
 CYP has projects across California, Mexico, Europe and Asia, including the 
redesign of the Balboa Bay Club in Newport Beach. 
</P>
