</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three D Departments Inc., a Costa Mesa operator of retail bed and bath 
specialty stores, posted a loss of $832,000, or 29 cents a share, for its 
latest fiscal quarter. That compared to a loss of $246,000, or 9 cents a share, 
for the same period a year earlier.Sales for the company's third quarter, which 
ended April 30, declined 5% to $8.6 million from $9.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
 For the first three quarters of its fiscal year, the company recorded a loss 
of $638,000, or 22 cents a share, compared to a loss of $64,000, or 2 cents a 
share, for the same period a year earlier. Nine-month sales slipped 5% to $31.3 
million from $33 million. The company attributed the sales decline to the 
closing of seven stores and earthquake damage to its Woodland Hills location. 
